@node intro "The Introduction"

@{b}@{u} What is it for?@{ub}@{uu}

	Here it its....... ehm..  what is? 

	Magic-saga   continues...  This   time  I  bring  you  a
	replacement   for   DLGUPLOAD  and  SUPERUP. 2  separate
	utilities brought by 2 separate authors.

	MagicUpload  is  simply a file uploader.  :-) Similar to
	the  routines  used  in  MagicFile.  But this is a stand
	alone version and a little simpler. 

	MagicUpload   was  written  because  DLGUpload  corrupts
	memory  in  my system.  Also, with MagicUpload you don't
	need another program for uploading with GUI.

	MagicUpload  can  upload files either privately to users
	directory or to standard DLG file areas.

	MagicUpload    has    also    internal    support    for
	@{"ReqTools-library" link reqtools}, easy to do multiple uploads once!

	MagicUpload     can     be     configured     to     use
	File_ID.DIZ-description   files   if  wanted.   External
	Config-file @{"MagicUpload.Config" link configfile}

	@{"Using MagicUpload from YaHoo (By Alan Bland)" link yahoo}

	@{u}It  DOES  NOT  need  DLGUpload or SUPERUP.  It's a stand
	alone program.@{uu}

@{b}@{fg highlight}
                       THIS IS A FREE PUBLIC DOMAIN PROGRAM
                         NO CHARGE IS REQUIRED WHEN USING
@{ub}@{fg text}
@endnode

@node require "Requirements"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

	 OS2.04  required  and  a  working,  properly  installed
	@{"Dialog Pro BBS" link dialog} BBS sofware!

	DLG.library  is  used.   And optionally ReqTools.library
	V38 if you want to use "GUI".

	 It was compiled with SAS/C V6.51 and should work nicely
	without Gurus or Crashes.

@endnode

@node dialog "What is DLG?"

 @{b}@{u}Hmm, DLG? What does it mean?@{ub}@{uu}

	 DLG stands for Dialog Professional BB/OS.  It's really amazing
	package  from  Telepro  Technologies.  There's so many features
	within this software so I won't start listing them here.

	 If  you  like  to  know more about DLG.  Call ANY BBS which is
	running with it.  I think you will see what I mean.

@endnode

@node reqtools "What is ReqTools"

 @{b}@{u}Reqtools?@{ub}@{uu}

	ReqTools.library  is  a great tool for making requestors
	in   your   program.    It   has   very   powerfull  and
	easy-to-program features.  Everyone should use Reqtools.

	Thanks  to  Nico  François  for programming the library.
	You  are  the  kind of person who keeps Amiga running on
	and on!

			  @{u}Thank you, Nico!@{uu}

	MagicUpload was developed with ReqTools V38.1266

@endnode

@node install "Installing CheckAlias"

 @{b}@{u}Great, But How do I install it?@{ub}@{uu}

	There is no need to do any complex install.  This can be
	used  from CLI. 

	However,  optionally  you can make a menuentry for this.
	For easy SYSOP upload from DLG's filemenu. 

	This is how I have configured it:

	[ 1] Letter:                   ~
	[ 2] Executable: (path/name)   DLGOWN:MagicUpload AREA=%File_AreaNumber
	[ 4] Description:              Sysop Upload
	[ 5] Type:                     Executable
	[ 6] Help File:                FILE_MAIN/~
	[ 7] Lower level:              255
	[ 8] Upper level:              255
	[ 9] Hidden:                   NO
	[10] Load type:                OVERLAY
	[11] Ask user if sure:         NO
	[12] Pend messages:            YES
	[13] Cli mode:                 YES
	[14] Pause on completion:      NO
	[15] Log value:                None
	[16] Activity string:          Sysop Uploading Files
	[17] Priority:                 DEFAULT
	[18] Edit help file

	This opens a requester to the BBS Screen and queries for
	files  to  upload.   MagicUpload  checks  if the user is
	LOCAL-user,  and does not let the requester open if user
	is a remote user (Port name is used for checking that, I
	check  the middle letter if it's L.  ie.  TL0 is a local
	user)

		@{"HIT HERE FOR EXAMPLES" link examples}

@endnode

@node paramet "Calling Parameters & Operation"

 @{b}@{u}Parameters passed to MagicUpload in Commandline@{ub}@{uu}

	MagicUpload   uses   ReadArgs  for  easy  and  powerfull
	commandline usage.  Here is how you can use it:

	Every  parameter can be inside ""-marks.  Parameters can
	be  specified  with or without keywords, if keywords are
	left       out,       the       order       must      be

	FILE,AREA,DESC,FROM,ATTR/N,DOWN/N,NOTEXT/S,GETDIZ/S,UPPER/S:

	Parameters  can  be  specified  with  or without = mark.
	Example:

	 MagicUpload FILE="ram:NiceModule.LHA"		or
	 MagicUpload FILE "ram:NiceModule.LHA"

 @{b}Parameters@{ub} (All optional)

	FILE	Filename to upload, if path is not given
		file will be uploaded from CURRENT DIR.
		If left out, ReqTools will be used!!
	AREA	Area to upload file to. Can be a user.
	DESC	Description for file. Max 300 chars.
	FROM	Uploaders name/id.
		Default is "MagicUpload"
	ATTR	File Attribute. 0=RATIO, 1=FREE, 
		2=UNVALIDATED. Default is 0.
	DOWN	How many times this has been downloaded.
		Default is 0.
	NOTEXT	Force MagicUpload NOT to print anything out.
		You need this if you don't start MUP
		from CLI!
	GETDIZ	Tries to get File_ID.DIZ with the proper
		program, defined in @{"MagicUpload.config" configfile}
	UPPER	Uppercase all filenames before upload.

		@{"HIT HERE FOR EXAMPLES" link examples}

@endnode

@node examples "Some examples"

 @{b}@{u}Some examples using MagicUpload!@{ub}@{uu}

	@{"Using MagicUpload from YaHoo (By Alan Bland)" link yahoo}

@{fg highlight}MagicUpload FILE=MAGUP084.LHA AREA=19 DESC="MagicUpload V0.84 by Erno Tuomainen"
@{fg text}
	Will  upload  a file MAGUP082.LHA from current directory
	to  area  number  19.   With the description given after
	DESC-keyword.

@{fg highlight}MagicUpload
@{fg text}
	If  no  parameters  are  defined,  MagicUpload  will use
	reqtools to ask everything.

@{fg highlight}MagicUpload AREA=19
@{fg text}
	Will  upload file(s) to area 19.  Reqtools filerequester
	will be used if available.

@{fg highlight}MagicUpload FILE=ram:MAGUP084.LHA
@{fg text}
	Will  upload  file  'ram:MAGUP084.LHA'  and ask the area
	with reqtools requester.

@{fg highlight}MagicUpload AREA="Jean Luc Picard"
@{fg text}
	Will  upload  file(s) to user Jean Luc Picard.  ReqTools
	will be used.

@{fg highlight}MagicUpload AREA=10 FILE=ENTERPRISE.ZIP GETDIZ
@{fg text}
	Will   upload   file   'Enterprise.ZIP'   (From  CURRENT
	directory)  to file area 10 and tries to get File_ID.DIZ
	and use it as file description (short+long)

@{fg highlight}MagicUpload ?
@{fg text}
	Display  some  help.   Press  RETURN again to get bigger
	help.

	@{"USING FROM DLG MENU AS A SYSOP LOCAL UPLOADER!" link install}

@endnode

@node yahoo "Using from YaHoo"

 @{b}@{u}Using MagicUpload from YaHoo!@{ub}@{uu}

	YaHoo is a great and very configurable node monitor made
	by  Alan Bland.  The advantage of this "monitor" is that
	it  REALLY IS configurable.  You can add almost anything
	into  it  and  create  a great BBS-handling utility.  So
	MagicUpload can now be used from there too.

@{u}Add the following line into DLGCONFIG:Misc/Yahoo.cfg@{uu}

	gad_glob Upload    DLGOWN:MagicUpload.030 NOTEXT

	NOTEXT  is  required, it forces MagicUpload NOT TO print
	anything out. 

@endnode

@node configfile "ConfigFile for MagicUpload"

 @{b}@{u}Config File!@{ub}@{uu}

	The optional configuration file is:

	@{u}DLGCONFIG:MISC/MagicUpload.config@{uu}

	This file defines all file types and programs to extract
	File_ID.DIZ from them.  The system I use is very similar
	as used in DuraDIZ.

	Please direct all output to >NIL:  or use Quiet mode.

@{b}Format of configfile:@{ub}

	First line:	PATTERN
	Second Line:	Command

	EDITOR  defines  the  editor  to be used for editing the
	long  file  description.  If this is left out, you can't
	edit the long description, naturally.  NOTE:  The editor
	MUST NOT return immediately it has been started!!!

	There can be up to 39 file types defined.  Don't add any
	BLANK lines.

	@{"Example Config File" link exaconfig}

@endnode

@node exaconfig "Example ConfigFile"

@{b}Example Config File:@{ub}

---CUT HERE---
EDITOR
dh3:miscutils/CED %s -KEEPIO
#?.LHA
dh3:miscutils/Lha -q e %s File_ID.DIZ
#?.LZH
dh3:miscutils/Lha -q e %s File_ID.DIZ
#?.DMS
dlgown:dmsdiz >NIL: x File_ID.DIZ %s
#?.ZIP
dh3:miscutils/unzip -o -qq %s File_ID.DIZ FILE_ID.DIZ
#?.JPG
dlgown:viewmate %s DESC >FILE_ID.DIZ
#?.JPEG
dlgown:viewmate %s DESC >FILE_ID.DIZ
#?.GIF
dlgown:viewmate %s DESC >FILE_ID.DIZ
---CUT HERE---
@endnode

