@node author "About the Author"

 @{b}@{u}Few words about the Author@{ub}@{uu}

	I  am  21 (born 11.12.1972) years old male and computers
	have  been my life since I was <10 years old.  I live in
	a small northern country called Finland, located between
	Russia and Sweden.

	You  should know that I am not mainly a PROGRAMMER, I am
	a  freelance  musician.   I  love  music,  I run a Music
	orientated  BBS (Moonlight Sonata) and I have made music
	since  I got my first computer (Aquarius I), after I got
	Commodore  C-64  my music hobby took a big step forward,
	MULTICHANNEL  MUSIC.  :) I started programming assembler
	with  C-64,  made  some  music compilations etc.  stuff.
	Then  couple  years later I bought my first Amiga (500),
	music hobby took again a BIG step forward.  I could make
	music  with  very realistic instruments, samples!  Again
	couple  years  later  I  bought more music equipment, my
	first synthesizer (Kawai K1/II), then couple years later
	I  bought 2 more synths.  Korg M1R and Korg 01/Wfd and A
	mixer..   thats  what  my setup is currently.  I compose
	synthesizer music (nothing published) as my hobby.
	I  hope  that someday I can publish some records with my
	music in them.

	But  I am also a programmer, I have programmed C-64 with
	assembler  and  basic.   And  Amiga/PC  with  Assembler,
	basic, Pascal and recently I have started to study C (by
	myself).  C is my kind of language, definitely.

