@node history "Program History"

What does it mean?

(RELD)	Released to public.
( ADD)  Something was added into the program.
(FIXD)  Something nasty was fixed.
(BUGN)  Bug noticed but NOT fixed, because I'm lazy too.
(RMVD)	Something was removed
(CHNG)  Something was changed in the soul of program...

 @{b}@{u}Short Version History@{ub}@{uu}

VERSION: (@{b}V0.86 09.09.1994@{ub}) - Lot's of requests

	( ADD)	File_ID.DIZ  support. This is accomplished with Config-
		File. @{"MagicUpload.config" link configfile}
		@{u}NOTE!   MagicUpload  will  not try to get File_ID.DIZ if
		GETDIZ (or GD) is NOT specified on the commandline.@{uu}
	( ADD)	Edit Long gadget and EDITOR line in Configuration file.
	( ADD)	UPPER  command line switch.  If specified, all filenames
		will be uppercased before upload.
	( ADD)	Two Environment variables:
		  @{u}MUP_FROM@{uu} = Name of the uploader
		  @{u}MUP_DESC@{uu} = Default description
		They both can be either Global or Local and will be read
		if NOT specified in the commandline (with DESC and FROM)
	( ADD)	UPS!   I  forgot  to  activate  the  DELETING  function.
		Before  when  you  pressed  "Up & Del" the file just got
		uploaded but source was not deleted.  Now it should work
	(CHNG)	If  Filename  is specified but no area, MagicUpload will
		ask  for  the  area  and perform a single Upload for the
		file  specified.   MagicUpload  can  now be used in some
		Directory  Utility  like  DirOpus  too!   (select file &
		press UPLOAD and you will be asked for area/user)
	(FIXD)	MagicUpload did not set the Result code to NULL (0) when
		program succeeded.  Fixed.
	(FIXD)	A  bug  which  made  uploading  from  Device  ROOT-paths
		impossible.   Ie.   if  you  tried to upload a file from
		RAM:  it failed.

		@{"HIT HERE FOR SOME EXAMPLES" link examples}

VERSION: (@{b}V0.84 08.09.1994@{ub}) - Small update

	( ADD)	AREA   keyword  is  no  more  required.   If  left  out,
		MagicUpload will ask for the file area.
	( ADD)	Area-gadget, can be used to change area for uploads.
	( ADD)	NOTEXT-option.   If  this  is specified, nothing will be
		printed out.
	(FIXD)	Two Enforcer-hits, (LONG READ FROM $0) Harmless. 

VERSION: (@{b}V0.82 05.09.1994@{ub}) - Again a new program

	(RELD)	The first release. 
	( ADD)	Public    &    Private    uploads    with   or   without
		ReqTools.library.    ReqTools   is   required  for  Bulk
		uploads.

@endnode
